<TITLE> HC gives notice on Liberation War sites </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 25 (bdnews24.com) - The High Court served a notice on the government on Thursday regarding preservation of two national heritage sites at Suhrawardy Uddyan. The two Liberation War sites mark the place where Sheikh Mujibur Rahman delivered his historic speech on Mar 7 in 1971, and where Pakistani occupation forces surrendered to the allied forces on Dec. 16. The court the government to show cause why a committee should not be formed anew to protect the sites and raze illegal structures, if any. The bench of justices ABM Khairul Haque and Momtaz Uddin Ahmed gave the order on a writ petition by liberation war sector commander AKM Shafiullah and historian Prof Muntasir Mamun. The court ordered the cabinet secretary, public works secretary, liberation war affairs secretary, and chief engineer and chief architect of the public works department to reply to the notice by the next hearing on July 6. Advocate Manzil Morshed appeared for the petitioners, while attorney general Mahbubey Alam represented the government. b
